Inter Milan striker, Lukaku, got both goals in the first half, one a penalty, to take him to 55 goals for Belgium. Birkir Saevarsson had equalised for Iceland but the hosts are looking at relegation to League B after losing all four games in the group so far. Belgium moved ahead of England after Gareth Southgate's side suffered a 1-0 loss against Denmark at Wembley. Denmark's win leaves them second in the group. --BBC--